Some Old Yet Simple Kanji
by Mike Cash » Sun 07.25.2010 12:40 am I took this photo of the back of a tombstone in a small private cemetery in rural Nagano Prefecture just especially to share with the Japanese learners here. There are two kanji visible which were formerly in common use (at least in inscriptions) and which are no longer used. You should be able to figure out both their readings and their meanings purely from context if you have studied kanji even a little bit.
Never underestimate my capacity for pettiness.
Mike Cash
